ably reproduce the main features of\nexperimental phase diagrams for T- and T$^{\\prime}$-cuprates and novel\nnickelates. The superconducting phase of cuprates/nickelates is determined by\nthe on-site composite boson transport, it is not a consequence of pairing of\ndoped holes/electrons, but represents one of the possible phase states of\nparent systems.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 2 Nov 2021 15:12:20 GMT"}],"update_date":"2022-03-30"}
