at the demarcation in the shear viscosity between the inner\n\"lubricating\" layer and the outer layer cultivates fluid slippage in the buffer\nlayer and an upward shift in the logarithmic layer; a hypothesis akin to DR\nusing wall lubrication and superhydrophobic surfaces.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 2 Nov 2021 15:31:39 GMT"}],"update_date":"2021-11-03"}
